item.title: Give Aid
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: ActionAid is a global movement of people working together to further human rights and defeat poverty for all. Visit their website to make a donation!

item.title: Support Victims
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Urgent relief efforts are underway after two major earthquakes in Nepal. Help International Medical Corps assist survivors with lifesaving medical supplies and care.

item.title: Help Children
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The children of Nepal desperately need your help. Help children in Nepal. Donate on UNICEF website for earthquake response. UNICEF has been on the ground working around the clock, mobilizing life-saving supplies since the first day of the devastating earthquake. Now, UNICEF is loading two cargo flights for urgent airlift to Kathmandu with a total of 120 tons of humanitarian aid including much needed medical and hospital supplies, tents and blankets.

item.title: Nepal is a Beautiful Country Surrounded by the Himalayan Range
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The Mountain Region (Himal), situated in the Great Himalayan Range, makes up the northern part of Nepal. It contains the highest elevations in the world including 8,848 metres (29,029 ft) height Mount Everest (Sagarmāthā in Nepali) on the border with China.

item.title: A 7.8 Magnitude Earthquake Hit Nepal on April 25...
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The number of people killed in Nepal by two major earthquakes has surpassed 8,500, making the disaster the deadliest to hit the Himalayan country on record, as rescuers are still searching for dozens of people missing in remote villages.
